  <section class="bg-gray-50 py-16"><div class="section"><div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
    <div>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">Stockton Fire Code Requirements</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">The City of Stockton enforces the California Fire Code (Title 19 CCR) through the Stockton Fire Department. As the seat of San Joaquin County and the Central Valley's largest city, Stockton oversees a diverse commercial landscape including the Downtown Stockton waterfront redevelopment, the Miracle Mile commercial corridor, extensive agricultural and food processing facilities, and significant warehouse and distribution operations along the I-5 and SR-99 corridors. California mandates automatic fire sprinklers in most new commercial construction statewide.</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">Stockton's food processing and agricultural industries create fire protection obligations that go beyond standard commercial requirements. Cold storage facilities, packing houses, and food manufacturing operations require specialized suppression systems and more frequent inspection cycles. The city's significant restaurant and food service concentration also generates a high volume of NFPA 96 kitchen suppression obligations across the metro area.</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">Key standards include <a href="/compliance/nfpa-10/" class="text-red-brand hover:underline">NFPA 10</a>, <a href="/compliance/nfpa-72/" class="text-red-brand hover:underline">NFPA 72</a>, and <a href="/compliance/nfpa-25/" class="text-red-brand hover:underline">NFPA 25</a>.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-200 mb-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-4">Stockton Fire Prevention Contacts</h3>
