  <section class="bg-gray-50 py-16"><div class="section max-w-3xl">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-8 text-center">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-5 border border-gray-200"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">What fire safety services are required for commercial buildings in Stockton, CA?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">Stockton enforces the California Fire Code (Title 19 CCR). Requirements include fire extinguishers (NFPA 10), fire alarms (NFPA 72), sprinklers (NFPA 13/25), and kitchen suppression for commercial cooking (NFPA 96). California mandates sprinklers in most new commercial construction.</p></div>
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-5 border border-gray-200"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">How often are fire inspections required in Stockton?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">The Stockton Fire Department conducts annual commercial property inspections. Fire extinguishers: monthly visual checks and annual professional inspection. Fire alarms: annual testing. Sprinklers: quarterly, semi-annual, and annual inspections. Kitchen suppression: semi-annual per NFPA 96.</p></div>
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-5 border border-gray-200"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">Does Stockton have specific fire code requirements for cold storage and food processing?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">Yes. Cold storage facilities, food packing operations, and food manufacturing plants in Stockton may be subject to NFPA 13 high-piled storage requirements, ammonia refrigeration system standards (NFPA 55), and specialized suppression requirements beyond standard commercial fire protection. Consult a licensed fire protection engineer for your specific facility type.</p></div>
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-5 border border-gray-200"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">Do restaurants in Stockton need special fire suppression systems?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">Yes. All commercial cooking producing grease-laden vapors requires a wet chemical suppression system per NFPA 96, plus a Class K extinguisher within 30 feet of cooking equipment. Systems must be inspected semi-annually by a licensed technician.</p></div>
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-5 border border-gray-200"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">Who enforces fire codes in Stockton, CA?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">The Stockton Fire Department enforces fire codes within Stockton city limits. The California State Fire Marshal's Office licenses fire protection contractors statewide at (916) 445-8200.</p></div>
    </div>
